resources.string: The cheetah (Acinonyx jubatus; /ˈtʃiːtə/) is a large cat of the subfamily Felinae that occurs in North, Southern and East " + "Africa, and a few localities in Iran. It inhabits a variety of mostly arid habitats like dry forests, scrub forests, " + "and savannahs. The species is IUCN Red Listed as Vulnerable, as it suffered a substantial decline in its historic range in the 20th century due to habitat" + " loss, poaching for the illegal pet trade, and conflict with humans. By 2016, the glob" + "al cheetah population has been estimated at approximately 7,100 individuals in the wild. Several African countries have taken steps to im" + "prove cheetah conservation measures.
